Mount a persistent local folder into the trainer service.

1. In docker-compose.yml, under trainer:, add:
volumes:
  - ./ml/artifacts:/app/ml/artifacts
So your trainer section should look roughly like:

  trainer:
    build: ./ml
    environment:
      DATABASE_URL: postgresql+psycopg2://${POSTGRES_USER:-ipl_user}:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD:-ipl_password}@postgres:5432/${POSTGRES_DB:-ipl_db}
      MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI: http://mlflow:5000
    depends_on:
      postgres:
        condition: service_healthy
    volumes:
      - ./data:/data
      - ./ml/artifacts:/app/ml/artifacts
    profiles: ["ml"]
